# Backend middleware

## Rate limiting

- When using a custom store with `express-rate-limit`, set `keyGenerator` to the library’s **`ipKeyGenerator`** (import from `express-rate-limit`).
- Do not build a custom IP-based key: the library handles IPv6 and `X-Forwarded-For` correctly; custom logic often fails validation (e.g. IPv6 format).

## Request ID

- Request ID middleware adds a correlation ID per request.
- Error responses include this ID in the JSON body for log correlation and debugging.

## Webhooks

- Validate signatures in middleware before running handler logic.
- Return immediately (fire-and-forget); process the webhook asynchronously so the caller does not time out and retry.
